# mulch — environment configuration
#
# mulch does not read environment variables at runtime. This file exists
# so contributors know the convention applies: copy `.env.example` to
# `.env` if/when mulch starts reading env vars. `.env` itself is
# gitignored; `.env.example` is committed and tracked.
#
# Note: `MULCH_DIR`, `MULCH_README`, `MULCH_HOOK`, `MULCH_HOOK_SECTION`,
# `MULCH_RECIPE_NAME`, and `MULCH_RECIPE_ACTION` are internal constants
# mulch *sets* (for lifecycle hooks and provider recipes), not values it
# reads from the environment. There is nothing to configure here.
